A local cache save allows users to to save the list of items added
in their local machine. Retrieval of the list upon relaunching the
application returns the saved list.

path for storing the cache file does not exist or is invalid.

the maintainers.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor code to improve code quality
commitResults.messageBody:
Better code quality can improve readability of the code. By making the
code more logical and easier to understand.

The code adheres to a logical structure. Magic numbers have been
drastically reduced/ removed. Complicated functions have been extracted
into separate functions adhering to SLAP principle. KISS principle have
also been applied to keep code easy to understand.

Assertions helps ensure invariants assumed hold at certain parts of the
code. This reduces the time needed to debug since assertions return
true at certain parts of the code.

in the case where the user adds whitespaces unintentionally causing the
find command to return nothing.

commitResults.messageBody:
The findEvent method is able to better match user input string by

when a keyword is matched

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor validateDateTime method of the DateParser class
commitResults.messageBody:
The method failed test cases where the input date time is equal to the
current date time. As such, a false positive result was produced.

The method now checks if the input time is equal to the current time and
returns the right output for it.

DateParser method lacked sufficient testing for the correct output on
edge cases. Doing so lowers the chance of bugs and introduces unit
testing on the methods.

More test is done using edge cases of the DateParser class, specifically
the case when the input date time are the same.

commitResults.messageBody:

Duplicates can confuse the user and affect user experience with the
application.
